    • FAQs

      Questions you may have, answered with
      • What are the key features to consider in an HP printer?
        When choosing an HP printer, consider print speed, resolution, and connectivity options. Print speed is measured in pages per minute (ppm), and higher speeds are beneficial for frequent or bulk printing. Resolution, measured in dots per inch (dpi), affects print quality, with higher dpi offering sharper images. Connectivity options like USB, Wi-Fi, or Ethernet determine how the printer can be connected to devices.
        How'd we do?

      • What are the differences between inkjet and laser HP printers?
        Inkjet printers are generally better for color-intensive printing, like photos, due to their ability to produce smooth color gradations. Laser printers excel in fast, high-volume printing and typically have lower per-page costs for black and white documents. Your choice should depend on your primary printing needs.
        How'd we do?
        Leave feedback about your eBay search experience - opens in new window or tabLeave feedback about your eBay search experience - opens in new window or tab
      • How does printer size and capacity impact usage?
        Consider the printer's size and paper handling capacity. Larger printers can handle more volume and often have features like multiple paper trays and higher monthly duty cycles, suitable for office environments. Compact models are ideal for personal or home office use where space and printing demands are limited.
